The following are some important links to learn how to create and type Jenkins Files:

1. https://www.lambdatest.com/blog/jenkins-declarative-pipeline-examples/

2. https://www.baeldung.com/ops/jenkins-conditional-constructs#:~:text=Effective%20Jenkins%20pipelines%20rely%20heavily,steps%2C%20or%20any%20other%20condition.

3. https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/pipeline/syntax/   # This is an official website to learn Jenkins Groovy script for pipeline 
  Topics to read in the above link:
    i. When
    ii. Post
    iii. Stages
    iv. Steps
    v. Environment
    vi. Parameters
    vii. Input
    ix. Options

4. https://crontab.guru/
